[{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = CoreformIGA","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#CoreformIGA","page":"Home","title":"CoreformIGA","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [CoreformIGA BasisBernstein]","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#CoreformIGA.BasisBernstein.B-Tuple{Array{Int64,1},Array{Float64,1}}","page":"Home","title":"CoreformIGA.BasisBernstein.B","text":"B(p, xi)\n\nReturn the value of the tensor product Bernstein basis of degree p evaluated at xi. This can be multidimensional and so both p and n are arrays to specify the basis order in each direction and the number of derivatives in each direction, respectively.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"index.html#CoreformIGA.BasisBernstein.B1d-Tuple{Int64,Float64}","page":"Home","title":"CoreformIGA.BasisBernstein.B1d","text":"B1d(p, xi)\n\nReturn the value of the 1d Bernstein basis of degree p evaluated at xi in 01.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"index.html#CoreformIGA.BasisBernstein.dBdxi-Tuple{Array{Int64,1},Array{Float64,1}}","page":"Home","title":"CoreformIGA.BasisBernstein.dBdxi","text":"dBdxi(p,xi)\n\nReturn the gradient of the tensor product Bernstein basis of degree p evaluated at xi. This can be multidimensional and so both p and n are arrays to specify the basis order in each direction and the number of derivatives in each direction, respectively.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"index.html#CoreformIGA.BasisBernstein.dBdxi1d-Tuple{Int64,Float64}","page":"Home","title":"CoreformIGA.BasisBernstein.dBdxi1d","text":"dBdxi1d(p, xi)\n\nReturn the first derivative of the 1d Bernstein basis of degree p evaluated at xi in 01.\n\nSee also: B1d(p, xi)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"index.html#CoreformIGA.BasisBernstein.dnBdxin-Tuple{Array{Int64,1},Array{Int64,1},Array{Float64,1}}","page":"Home","title":"CoreformIGA.BasisBernstein.dnBdxin","text":"dnBdxin(p, n, xi)\n\nReturn the nth derivative of the tensor product Bernstein basis of degree p evaluated at xi. This can be multidimensional and so both p and n are arrays to specify the basis order in each direction and the number of derivatives in each direction, respectively.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"index.html#CoreformIGA.BasisBernstein.dnBdxin1d-Tuple{Int64,Int64,Float64}","page":"Home","title":"CoreformIGA.BasisBernstein.dnBdxin1d","text":"dnBdxin1d(p, n, xi)\n\nReturn the nth derivative of the 1d Bernstein basis of degree p evaluated at xi in 01.\n\nSee also: dBdxi1d(p, xi)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
